name: When is the first day of fall
summary: The first day of fall, also known as the autumnal equinox, is approaching. In 2024, it will occur on September 22nd at 9:21 PM Eastern Time. The autumnal equinox marks the transition from summer to fall, when the day and night are of equal length all over the world. It also signals the end of Daylight Saving Time, which will end on November 3rd, 2024. People can celebrate the autumnal equinox by observing the changing colors of leaves, going for walks in nature, or participating in traditional rituals such as lighting candles or burning sage.

name: Mercury Morris
summary: Mercury Morris, a legendary running back and member of the undefeated 1972 Miami Dolphins team, has passed away at the age of 77. Morris was known for his elusive rushing style and was a key contributor to the Dolphins' undefeated season and two Super Bowl victories. He played for the Dolphins from 1969 to 1976, and his jersey number, 42, has been retired by the team in his honor. Morris was inducted into the Dolphins' Ring of Honor in 1991 and was a member of the Pro Football Hall of Fame's All-1970s Team. His passing has been met with an outpouring of grief and remembrance from former teammates, fans, and the football community.
